54struct CallReceiveStatistics {
55 unsigned int cumulativeLost;
56 unsigned int jitterSamples;
57 int64_t rttMs;
58 int64_t payload_bytes_rcvd = 0;
59 int64_t header_and_padding_bytes_rcvd = 0;
60 int packetsReceived;
61 // The capture NTP time (in local timebase) of the first played out audio
62 // frame.
63 int64_t capture_start_ntp_time_ms_;
64 // The timestamp at which the last packet was received, i.e. the time of the
65 // local clock when it was received - not the RTP timestamp of that packet.
66 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-lastpacketreceivedtimestamp
67 absl::optional<int64_t> last_packet_received_timestamp_ms;
68 // Remote outbound stats derived by the received RTCP sender reports.
69 // Note that the timestamps below correspond to the time elapsed since the
70 // Unix epoch.
71 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#remoteoutboundrtpstats-dict*
72 absl::optional<int64_t> last_sender_report_timestamp_ms;
73 absl::optional<int64_t> last_sender_report_remote_timestamp_ms;
74 uint32_t sender_reports_packets_sent = 0;
75 uint64_t sender_reports_bytes_sent = 0;
76 uint64_t sender_reports_reports_count = 0;
77};
78
79namespace voe {
80
81class ChannelSendInterface;
82
83// Interface class needed for AudioReceiveStream tests that use a
84// MockChannelReceive.
85
86class ChannelReceiveInterface : public RtpPacketSinkInterface {
87 public:
88 virtual ~ChannelReceiveInterface() = default;
89
90 virtual void SetSink(AudioSinkInterface* sink) = 0;
91
92 virtual void SetReceiveCodecs(
93 const std::map<int, SdpAudioFormat>& codecs) = 0;
94
95 virtual void StartPlayout() = 0;
96 virtual void StopPlayout() = 0;
97
98 // Payload type and format of last received RTP packet, if any.
99 virtual absl::optional<std::pair<int, SdpAudioFormat>> GetReceiveCodec()
100 const = 0;
101
102 virtual void ReceivedRTCPPacket(const uint8_t* data, size_t length) = 0;
103
104 virtual void SetChannelOutputVolumeScaling(float scaling) = 0;
105 virtual int GetSpeechOutputLevelFullRange() const = 0;
106 // See description of "totalAudioEnergy" in the WebRTC stats spec:
107 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcmediastreamtrackstats-totalaudioenergy
108 virtual double GetTotalOutputEnergy() const = 0;
109 virtual double GetTotalOutputDuration() const = 0;
110
111 // Stats.
112 virtual NetworkStatistics GetNetworkStatistics(
113 bool get_and_clear_legacy_stats) const = 0;
114 virtual AudioDecodingCallStats GetDecodingCallStatistics() const = 0;
115
116 // Audio+Video Sync.
117 virtual uint32_t GetDelayEstimate() const = 0;
118 virtual bool SetMinimumPlayoutDelay(int delay_ms) = 0;
119 virtual bool GetPlayoutRtpTimestamp(uint32_t* rtp_timestamp,
120 int64_t* time_ms) const = 0;
121 virtual void SetEstimatedPlayoutNtpTimestampMs(int64_t ntp_timestamp_ms,
122 int64_t time_ms) = 0;
123 virtual absl::optional<int64_t> GetCurrentEstimatedPlayoutNtpTimestampMs(
124 int64_t now_ms) const = 0;
125
126 // Audio quality.
127 // Base minimum delay sets lower bound on minimum delay value which
128 // determines minimum delay until audio playout.
129 virtual bool SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(int delay_ms) = 0;
130 virtual int GetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs() const = 0;
131
132 // Produces the transport-related timestamps; current_delay_ms is left unset.
133 virtual absl::optional<Syncable::Info> GetSyncInfo() const = 0;
134
135 virtual void RegisterReceiverCongestionControlObjects(
136 PacketRouter* packet_router) = 0;
137 virtual void ResetReceiverCongestionControlObjects() = 0;
138
139 virtual CallReceiveStatistics GetRTCPStatistics() const = 0;
140 virtual void SetNACKStatus(bool enable, int max_packets) = 0;
141
142 virtual AudioMixer::Source::AudioFrameInfo GetAudioFrameWithInfo(
143 int sample_rate_hz,
144 AudioFrame* audio_frame) = 0;
145
146 virtual int PreferredSampleRate() const = 0;
147
148 // Sets the source tracker to notify about "delivered" packets when output is
149 // muted.
150 virtual void SetSourceTracker(SourceTracker* source_tracker) = 0;
151
152 // Associate to a send channel.
153 // Used for obtaining RTT for a receive-only channel.
154 virtual void SetAssociatedSendChannel(
155 const ChannelSendInterface* channel) = 0;
156
157 // Sets a frame transformer between the depacketizer and the decoder, to
158 // transform the received frames before decoding them.
159 virtual void SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(
160 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::FrameTransformerInterface>
161 frame_transformer) = 0;
162};
163
164std::unique_ptr<ChannelReceiveInterface> CreateChannelReceive(
165 Clock* clock,
166 ProcessThread* module_process_thread,
167 NetEqFactory* neteq_factory,
168 AudioDeviceModule* audio_device_module,
169 Transport* rtcp_send_transport,
170 RtcEventLog* rtc_event_log,
171 uint32_t local_ssrc,
172 uint32_t remote_ssrc,
173 size_t jitter_buffer_max_packets,
174 bool jitter_buffer_fast_playout,
175 int jitter_buffer_min_delay_ms,
176 bool jitter_buffer_enable_rtx_handling,
177 rtc::scoped_refptr<AudioDecoderFactory> decoder_factory,
178 absl::optional<AudioCodecPairId> codec_pair_id,
179 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor,
180 const webrtc::CryptoOptions& crypto_options,
181 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer);
182
183} // namespace voe
184} // namespace webrtc
